The returning officer for the state, Charles Esimone, who announced the results on Tuesday in Owerri said that Obi scored 352,904 while Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress scored 66,171 votes while Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party polled 30,044 votes. The presidential candidate of the Labour Party, Mr Peter Obi has been declared the winner of the Saturday's presidential elections as conducted in Imo State.
The returning officer for the state, Charles Esimone, who announced the results on Tuesday in Owerri said that Obi scored 352,904 while Bola Tinubu of the All Progressives Congress scored 66,171 votes while Atiku Abubakar of the Peoples Democratic Party polled 30,044 votes.Â 
The New Nigeria People's Party candidate, Rabiu Kwankwaso scored 1,536 votes to come a distant fourth.
The returning officer said that the result of the Njaba LGA was not collated because of violence.